  "docs": {
    "sections": [
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Return the sum of array elements over a given axis treating Not a Numbers (NaNs) as zero."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Summary"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "In NumPy versions <= 1.9.0 Nan is returned for slices that are all-NaN or\nempty. In later versions zero is returned."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Extended Summary"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "Array containing numbers whose sum is desired. If "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "a"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " is not an\narray, a conversion is attempted."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "array_like",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "Array containing numbers whose sum is desired. If "
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "a"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": " is not an\narray, a conversion is attempted."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "a",
                "type": "field_list"
              },
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "Axis or axes along which the sum is computed. The default is to compute the\nsum of the flattened array."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "{int, tuple of int, None}, optional",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "Axis or axes along which the sum is computed. The default is to compute the\nsum of the flattened array."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "axis",
                "type": "field_list"
              },
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "The type of the returned array and of the accumulator in which the\nelements are summed.  By default, the dtype of "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "a"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " is used.  An\nexception is when "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "a"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " has an integer type with less precision than\nthe platform (u)intp. In that case, the default will be either\n(u)int32 or (u)int64 depending on whether the platform is 32 or 64\nbits. For inexact inputs, dtype must be inexact."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "data-type, optional",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "The type of the returned array and of the accumulator in which the\nelements are summed.  By default, the dtype of "
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "a"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": " is used.  An\nexception is when "
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "a"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": " has an integer type with less precision than\nthe platform (u)intp. In that case, the default will be either\n(u)int32 or (u)int64 depending on whether the platform is 32 or 64\nbits. For inexact inputs, dtype must be inexact."
